1546   070A             ;
1547   070A             ; AT 'EXEC', DE SHOULD POINT TO THE STRING AND HL SHOULD POINT
1548   070A             ; TO THE TABLE-1.  AT 'DIRECT', DE SHOULD POINT TO THE STRING.
1549   070A             ; HL WILL BE SET UP TO POINT TO TAB1-1, WHICH IS THE TABLE OF
1550   070A             ; ALL DIRECT AND STATEMENT COMMANDS.
1551   070A             ;
1552   070A             ; A '.' IN THE STRING WILL TERMINATE THE TEST AND THE PARTIAL
1553   070A             ; MATCH WILL BE CONSIDERED AS A MATCH.  E.G., 'P.', 'PR.',
1554   070A             ; 'PRI.', 'PRIN.', OR 'PRINT' WILL ALL MATCH 'PRINT'.
1555   070A             ;
1556   070A             ; THE TABLE CONSISTS OF ANY NUMBER OF ITEMS.  EACH ITEM
1557   070A             ; IS A STRING OF CHARACTERS WITH BIT 7 SET TO 0 AND
1558   070A             ; A JUMP ADDRESS STORED HI-LOW WITH BIT 7 OF THE HIGH
1559   070A             ; BYTE SET TO 1.
1560   070A             ; This is done by the macro 'DWA'.
1561   070A             ; If the program is executed from an address < 0x8000
1562   070A             ; take care to mask this bit in program part 'EXEC'.
1563   070A             ;
1564   070A             ; END OF TABLE IS AN ITEM WITH A JUMP ADDRESS ONLY.  IF THE
1565   070A             ; STRING DOES NOT MATCH ANY OF THE OTHER ITEMS, IT WILL
1566   070A             ; MATCH THIS NULL ITEM AS DEFAULT.
